Trudeau said it will keep people on both sides of the border safe amid the pandemic.
It will ensure we continue to get essential goods and services back and forth across the border,” Trudeau said.
The U.S. and Canada agreed last month to limit border crossings to essential travel amid the pandemic, but that agreement was due to expire this coming week.
Canada sends 75% of its exports to the U.S. and about 18% of American exports go to Canada.
The U.S. Canada border is world’s longest between two nations.